PC Number: 2020-0582

Date: 2020-08-23

Her Excellency the Governor General in Council, on the recommendation of the Minister of Industry, pursuant to subsection 12(2) of the Bankruptcy and Insolvency Act, appoints the following officers of the Office of the Superintendent of Bankruptcy of the Department of Industry to hold office during pleasure as official receivers for all bankruptcy districts and divisions in Canada:

 

(a) Funmilayo Balogun of Calgary, Alberta;

(b) Marie-Ève Bisaillon of Gatineau, Quebec;

(c) Juan Bituin of Edmonton, Alberta;

(d) Ellen Brongers of Vancouver, British Columbia;

(e) Mung Wai (Yume) Cheng of Vancouver, British Columbia;

(f) Ann Chu of Vancouver, British Columbia;

(g) Jodie Cook of Greenfield Park, Quebec;

(h) Andoni De Vega of Montréal, Quebec;

(i) Sophia El Hakkat of Brossard, Quebec;

(j) Khadeja Elsibai of Woodbridge, Ontario;

(k) Julie Diane Fay of Toronto, Ontario;

(l) James Gallinger of Toronto, Ontario;

(m) Adedayo Jegede of Edmonton, Alberta;

(n) Lara Kwitco of Hampstead, Quebec;

(o) Diana Lam of Repentigny, Quebec;

(p) Luc-André Larocque of Gatineau, Quebec;

(q) Raquel McGee of Stouffville, Ontario;

(r) Danielle Vanessa Ngueumdjeu Chekem of Québec, Quebec;

(s) Satinder Nijjar of Edmonton, Alberta;

(t) Chan Hong (Danny) Park of Vancouver, British Columbia;

(u) Carmelo Ramirez of Vancouver, British Columbia;

(v) Josée Ruel of Lévis, Quebec;

(w) Charles Skelton of Toronto, Ontario;

(x) Brendan Smith of Halifax, Nova Scotia; and

(y) Brandon Veit of Ottawa, Ontario.


 

Sur recommandation du ministre de l’Industrie et en vertu du paragraphe 12(2) de la Loi sur la faillite et l’insolvabilité, Son Excellence la Gouverneure générale en conseil nomme en qualité de séquestres officiels, à titre amovible, pour tous les districts et toutes les divisions des faillites au Canada, les fonctionnaires ci-après du Bureau du surintendant des faillites du ministère de l’Industrie :
